Class Session

  • java.lang.Object
    • pl.zankowski.yahoofinanceapi.Session

  • public class Session
extends java.lang.Object

    Date: 19.09.2015

    This class is a main class of Yahoo Finance API. It handles and process all data requests made by users.

    Wojciech Zankowski

    • Method Detail

      • reqMarketData

        public void reqMarketData(int requestID,
                          Contract contract,
                          java.util.List<DataRequest> dataRequestList)
                   throws RequestException
        This method handles Market Data requests to Yahoo Finance API. For every DataRequest is created task that download and parse data. If delay in DataRequest equals 0 then task is called only at the beginning and it's not scheduled for future execution.
        Parameters:
        requestID - Unique requestID that will let identify provided data in implementation of DataReceiver.
        contract - Contract objects containing instrument and exchange code.
        dataRequestList - List of data that has to be requested from Yahoo Finance API.
        Throws:
        RequestException - Thrown when requestID is not unique.

      • reqCustomData

        public void reqCustomData(int requestID,
                          java.lang.String instruments,
                          java.lang.String dataTypes,
                          int delay)
                   throws RequestException
        This method handles Custom Data requests to Yahoo Finance API. It allows to create unrestricted data request from Yahoo Finance API. If delay value is equal to 0 then data is downloaded only once.
        Parameters:
        requestID - Unique requestID that will let identify provided data in implementation of DataReceiver
        instruments - Instruments list in format appropriate for Yahoo Finance API. It can be obtained using RequestUtils.toInstruments(Contract...).
        dataTypes - Data list in format appropriate for Yahoo Finance API. It can be obtained using RequestUtils.toDataTypes(DataType...).
        delay - Delay between scheduled task calls. If 0 then task is called only once.
        Throws:
        RequestException - Thrown when requestID is not unique.

      • reqHistoricalData

        public void reqHistoricalData(int requestID,
                              Contract contract,
                              java.time.LocalDate startDate,
                              java.time.LocalDate endDate)
                       throws java.io.IOException
        This method requests Historical Data from Yahoo Finance API and streams it to DataReceiver. It calls request with default Daily interval.
        Parameters:
        requestID - Unique requestID that will let identify provided data in implementation of DataReceiver
        contract - Contract objects containing instrument and exchange code.
        startDate - Start date of data.
        endDate - End date of data.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • reqIntradayData

        public void reqIntradayData(int requestID,
                            Contract contract)
                     throws java.io.IOException
        This method handles Intraday data requests. Because of Yahoo Finance limitations it allows to download only data from last 5 days.
        Parameters:
        requestID - Unique requestID that will let identify provided data in implementation of DataReceiver
        contract - Contract objects containing instrument and exchange code.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • reqForexData

        public void reqForexData(int requestID,
                         ForexCurrency fromCurrency,
                         ForexCurrency toCurrency,
                         int delay)
                  throws RequestException
        This method handles Forex data requests. If delay equals 0 then task is called only at the beginning and it's not scheduled for future execution.
        Parameters:
        requestID - Unique requestID that will let identify provided data in implementation of DataReceiver
        fromCurrency - First of currency pair.
        toCurrency - Second of currency pair.
        delay - Delay between scheduled task calls. If 0 then task is called only once.
        Throws:
        RequestException - Thrown when requestID is not unique.
